<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The President to the Ambassador in
                        the Soviet Union (
                        Harriman
                    )Sent to the United States Naval
                        Attaché, Moscow, via Navy channels. For the full text of the message, see
                            ante, pp. 6–7.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Malta</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d248</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">248</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1944-10-04T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1944-10-04T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="248" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d248">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the Ambassador in
                        the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HWA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="2" xml:id="d248fn2">Sent to the United States Naval
                        Attaché, Moscow, via Navy channels. For the full text of the message, see
                            <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_6">pp. 6</ref>–<ref target="#pg_7">7</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Excerpts]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-04">4 October
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 76. Top Secret and Personal from the President to Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName>.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Will you please deliver the following message to Marshal <persName corresp="#p_S16">Stalin</persName> at once:</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>You will, by this time, have received from General <persName corresp="#p_D1">Deane</persName>, the statement of our Combined Chiefs of Staff position
                    relative to the war against Japan<note n="3" xml:id="d248fn3">The President
                        evidently was referring to the Joint Chiefs of Staff position alluded to <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>.</note> and I want to reiterate to you how
                    completely I accept the assurances which you have given us on this point. Our
                    three countries are waging a successful war against Germany and we can surely
                    join together with no less success in crushing a nation that I am sure in my
                    heart is as great an enemy of Russia as she is of ours.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
